  <refnamediv id='name'>
    <refname>ipsec checknss</refname>
    <refpurpose>Check or initialize the IPsec NSS database</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <!-- body begins here -->
  <refsynopsisdiv id='synopsis'>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>ipsec</command>
      <arg choice='plain'>checknss</arg>
      <arg choice='opt'>--nssdir <replaceable>@@IPSEC_NSSDIR@@</replaceable></arg>
      <arg choice='opt'>--settrusts </arg>
      <sbr/>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1 id='description'>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
      <emphasis remap='I'>Checknss</emphasis> checks or initialises the NSS
      database where all private keys for RSA and certificate keypairs are
      stored. To remove an existing IPsec NSS database, remove all the *.db
      files and pkcs11.txt from the NSS data directory (default: @@IPSEC_NSSDIR@@).
      If database exists returns successfully.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

